items.title: Officials discover a million more documents potentially related to Epstein case
items.description: The US Department of Justice says reviewing the material could delay release by a "few more weeks".

items.title: Explosion hits packed mosque in Nigeria
items.description: Eyewitnesses say the blast happened as people were gathered for evening prayers.

items.title: Democratic board member muted during Kennedy Center vote sues to remove Trump's name
items.description: US Representative Joyce Beatty claims the renaming of the venue is illegal because the change requires "an act of Congress".

items.title: Algerian law declares France's colonisation a crime
items.description: Lawmakers unanimously approve a law, which demands an apology and reparations from the former colonial power.

items.title: Two police officers killed in explosion in Moscow
items.description: A device was detonated after police approached a "suspicious" individual in Moscow, authorities said.
